The paper deals with distributed computation on graphs, specifically the problem of graph reconstruction in the congested clique model. This falls under the area of distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves analyzing the communication complexity of the algorithm, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The congested clique model is a well-known model in distributed computing, so the paper could also be classified under the sub-category of congested clique (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the properties of different graph classes, which falls under the area of graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
